article.description: — Sean Moore's 23 points helped Fairleigh Dickinson defeat St. Francis (PA) 81-71 on Monday night.
article.headline: Moore scores 23, leads Fairleigh Dickinson over St. Francis (PA) 81-71
article.linkText: Moore scores 23, leads Fairleigh Dickinson over St. Francis (PA) 81-71
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. -- — Sean Moore's 23 points helped Fairleigh Dickinson defeat St. Francis (PA) 81-71 on Monday night. Moore added eight rebounds for the Knights (8-11, 2-2 Northeast Conference). Terrence Brown scored 17 points, shooting 6 for 11 (2 for 3 from 3-point range) and 3 of 5 from the free throw line. Ansley Almonor shot 4 for 9 (4 for 7 from 3-point range) and 5 of 6 from the free throw line to finish with 17 points. Cam Gregory finished with 25 points and four assists for the Red Flash (5-12, 0-4). Eli Wilborn totaled 14 points, 11 rebounds and four assists. Bobby Rosenberger III had eight points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
